Text.string: Need help with something!
Our colleague's run away.
Or do.
No! Plus, if you don't kill him, Tern gives you a shiny piece of Eridium at the end of every session! Anyone who gives you a crystal is definitely legit.
Greetings, prospective patient. I sense why Sparrow and Grouse sent you, and I can help. But first, are you in a consciousness-centered place and prepared for growth?
Um, yeah.
Sure I am.
Always.
I've got a loooaaad of issues, and... whatnot.
Ah, but is your energy properly aligned? Let me observe your energy-flow for a moment.
Sure.
Okay.
Fine.
All righty.
I'm sensing that you have a very stressful work environment, and that you feel the fate of the universe rests on your shoulders. Interesting. Now, I see your energy is flowing. Keep aligning...
This is stupid.
Yep. Aligning. Got it.
This is foolish.
I'm trying, damn it!
Slightly more to the left...
Will you just open the door?
Ugh. Just let me in.
Open the door already.
Just let me in, would ya?

So, we gave all of Typhon's research data to this healer bot named Tern, but now he's gone off and started his own practice. If Maliwan gets him, they'll find all that data and come kill us! You gotta go to his office and get it back!
There we are. You are now properly aligned and prepared for healing. Please, enter my sanctum.
Remember, this is a sanctified space where all lifeforms can coexist harmoniously.
Sure. Whatever.
I'm always in harmony.
If you say so.
Oh, the world'll kick you in the pants for thinkin' a thing like that.
Your first diagnostic session is free. After that, I charge a nominal fee of one thousand dollars per cosmic realignment. Now, to begin: please lie on the couch.
Um. I can't do that.
Yeah, not sure I can do that.
I am unable to do that.
Ah, yeah. Can't do that.
As you wish. Your path will take you where it must. Anyway, we'll move on.
Now I'd like you to express yourself creatively. It exfoliates the soul. Use that paint there, and just go nuts on the canvas.
Yes, excellent! Now paint whatever is in your heart. Your soul's heart.
I see... From your artwork, I sense you feel stuck in an endless loop of violence and material acquisition. Interesting.
I know just the thing to break your cycle. A magnificent gift, just for you. Please, open the Box of Tranquility for a glorious reward in recognition of all your hard work today.
Awww, how unfortunate. Not what you were expecting? And how did that make you feel?
It made me FEEL like you're an asshole.
Like... you're a prick.
That you are something of a jerk.
“How did it make me feel,” he says. Well, that you're a right asshole is how.

Yes. Yes! You're expressing yourself. It's time to start your treatment. Listen carefully. You must trust me completely for the treatment to work. Under no circumstances should you resort to violence.
I dunno...
Uh, we'll see.
Perhaps.
No promises.
I want to be crystal clear. We cannot walk the path to healing hand-in-hand with barriers between us. I will let down my guard, and so must you. Do not shoot me, I cannot stress that enough.
Please do not resort to violence. This is for your own good!
You're doing very well. But the treatment must continue!
Admirable job, friend. Continue to remain peaceful.
You have to trust me! Do NOT shoot!

I'm so proud of you. You faced your death with fearlessness, and now your diagnostic is complete. I look forward to our future sessions. Now, I know that Grouse is concerned about the safety of the lab, so here is my memory core with all of Typhon's research on it. I no longer have need of it. The bots will be safe.
Tern is a threat to our very survival. If Maliwan gets a hold of that data, they will find us. You need to kill that idiot and scavenge his memory core.
And here is your complimentary Eridium crystal for being such a good patient. Go now, and be at peace. Namaste.
How'd it go, buddy?
Did you kill that annoying jerk or what?
Of course they didn't kill him! Why WOULD they have?
Because he's quite annoying.
Well I, for one, am glad that Tern is not dead. Thank you, Vault Hunter. I've got an extra big reward for showing your compassionate side.
Compassion is for bitrot-brained idiots.
Well, call me an idiot, then!
You're an idiot.
I should have known you weren't ready for treatment!
What? Don't kill him! He's a super nice guy and a great listener! He's even helping me deal with this absolute dickbag who's always creating a hostile work environment.
You'll never achieve harmony acting like that!
You're a terrible patient!
My sensors indicate you got the memory core. Good work. Come on back.
How'd it go, buddy?
Didn't you feel the signal burst? They killed Tern is how it went.
Why would they do THAT?!
Because he's quite annoying. Or... was.
Good riddance. The only thing crystals are good for is high-precision internal timekeeping. And some are quite... pretty.
Why are you so mean, Grouse?
This was a matter of survival, Sparrow. When are you going to start taking things seriously?
Well, would you rather be happy, or alive?
Never! What's the point of life if you have to take EVERYTHING seriously all the time?
You're hopeless.
Now stay RIGHT THERE! I need you to trust me!
And now, it is time for your rebirth!
Ouch! That hurts!
Well... I am sorry he got killed, but at least the data is safe.
What a weird question! So far, I've always been both!
Come to Tern's Aura Centering Center for a free energy-alignment session with me, Tern. Healing is on the horizon.
So, listen—Tern's a MASTER healer. His ideas are a little out there, but just roll with it. Use the intercom and tell him whatever he needs to hear. Oh, and... PLEASE don't kill him.
